BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 210.0 720 Td (Chapter 2: My Layers) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (I am not the same all the way through! I have layers, like an egg or an onion.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (My outside layer \(the crust\) is thin and rocky - you live on it!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Beneath that is my mantle - thick, hot, and slowly flowing like thick honey.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Deep inside is my outer core - liquid metal, so hot it glows!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (At my very center is my inner core - solid iron and nickel, hotter than the Sun's surface!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Each of my layers is important and makes me the special planet I am.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: EARTH'S LAYERS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Crust: 5-70 km thick. Thin and solid. Ocean crust is thinner than continental crust.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Mantle: 2,900 km thick. Hot rock that flows very slowly \(like toothpaste\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Outer Core: 2,200 km thick. Liquid iron and nickel. Creates Earth's magnetic field!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Inner Core: 1,200 km radius. Solid iron ball. Temperature: 9,800F \(hotter than Sun's surface!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (The deeper you go, the hotter it gets - about 25C per km in the crust!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* If Earth were an apple, the crust would be thinner than the apple's skin!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* The deepest hole ever drilled \(Kola Superdeep\) went only 7.6 miles - barely scratching the crust!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Earth's liquid outer core generates the magnetic field that protects us from solar radiation.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Cut a hard-boiled egg in half: shell=crust, white=mantle, yolk=core. Earth is like a giant egg!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (How do scientists know what is inside Earth if we cannot dig that deep?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
