BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 186.0 720 Td (Chapter 3: My Moving Skin) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Here is a secret: my skin \(crust\) is not one solid piece. It is broken into plates!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (These huge plates float on my mantle and move very slowly - about as fast as your fingernails grow.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Where plates bump together, mountains push up! Where they pull apart, valleys form!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Sometimes plates slide past each other and get stuck. When they slip - EARTHQUAKE!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (My plates have been moving for billions of years, rearranging continents like puzzle pieces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Africa and South America used to be joined together - you can see how they fit!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: PLATE TECTONICS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Earth's crust is broken into about 15 major tectonic plates that slowly move.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Convection currents in the hot mantle push and pull the plates \(like a pot of boiling soup\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Convergent boundaries: plates collide - mountains form \(Himalayas!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Divergent boundaries: plates pull apart - new crust forms \(Mid-Atlantic Ridge\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Transform boundaries: plates slide past each other - earthquakes \(San Andreas Fault\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Plates move 1-10 cm per year - about as fast as your fingernails grow!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* The Himalayas grow about 1 cm taller every year as India pushes into Asia!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* 250 million years from now, scientists predict the continents will rejoin into 'Pangaea Ultima.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* About 500,000 earthquakes are detected each year, but only 100,000 can be felt.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Put crackers on pudding. Push them together \(mountains form!\) and pull apart \(rift!\). That is plate tectonics!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (If continents are still moving, what will the world map look like in 100 million years?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
