BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 166.8 720 Td (Chapter 6: My Rock Collection) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (I have the most amazing rock collection! Three types of rocks, endlessly recycling.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (When my volcanoes cool their lava, I make igneous rocks - born from fire!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (When wind and water wear rocks into tiny pieces that settle in layers, I make sedimentary rocks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (And when heat and pressure squeeze and bake existing rocks, I make metamorphic rocks!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (These three types keep changing into each other - it is called the rock cycle!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (A rock on the ground today might have been lava, then sand, then squeezed into marble!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: THE ROCK CYCLE) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Igneous rocks: formed from cooled magma/lava \(granite, basalt, obsidian\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Sedimentary rocks: formed from layers of compressed sediment \(sandstone, limestone, shale\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Metamorphic rocks: changed by extreme heat and pressure \(marble, slate, quartzite\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (The rock cycle: any rock type can become any other type given enough time!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Igneous melts -> sediment erodes -> metamorphic gets squeezed -> melts again = cycle!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* The oldest known rock on Earth is 4.03 billion years old \(found in Canada\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Diamonds are metamorphic - carbon squeezed under extreme pressure deep underground!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Fossils are found in sedimentary rocks because layers bury dead organisms over time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Collect 3 rocks. Try to identify: Is each one igneous, sedimentary, or metamorphic? Use a guide!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (If all rocks are constantly recycling, could the sand on a beach today have once been a volcano?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
