BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 186.0 720 Td (Chapter 7: My Living Coat) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The best thing about me? I am covered in LIFE! From deserts to jungles to frozen poles!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (I have rainforests so thick with life that millions of species live in them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (I have deserts where clever animals survive with almost no water at all!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (I have frozen tundra where polar bears and penguins thrive in extreme cold.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (And my oceans are bursting with life from surface to deepest trench!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (All these different regions are called biomes - each one is a unique world of life!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: EARTH'S BIOMES) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Tropical Rainforest: warm, wet, most biodiversity. Contains 50% of all species!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Desert: dry \(less than 10 inches rain/year\), hot days, cold nights.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Tundra: freezing, permafrost, short summers, hardy plants and animals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Temperate Forest: four seasons, deciduous trees that lose leaves in fall.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Ocean: largest biome, covering 71% of Earth, from warm coral reefs to icy depths.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (An ecosystem is all the living and non-living things interacting in one area.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Scientists estimate 8.7 million species exist on Earth - but only 1.2 million have been identified!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Rainforests produce 28% of the world's oxygen despite covering only 6% of land.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Biodiversity = more types of life. It makes ecosystems stronger and more resilient.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Create an 'ecosystem in a jar': put soil, small plants, and a little water in a sealed jar. Watch it self-sustain!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why is biodiversity important? What happens when too many species disappear?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
